      <hedline>
        <hl1>George Divoky's Planet</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eric Julber article on Jan 6 article about Arctic sci</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Divoky has observed 27 years of global warming on his Arctic island, but that does not prove it is caused by ''our endless consumption of fossil fuels.'' It now appears that Mars -- without S.U.V.'s or oil drilling -- is also in a period of global warming.</p>
        <p>We share one major similarity with Mars: we both are heated by the same sun. Could it be?</p>
        <p>Eric Julber  Carmel, Calif.</p>
      </block>
